  <static seed="130" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring490.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{81y^{4}-16}=</m> <fillin characters="27" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(3y-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(3y+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(9y^{2}+4\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Note that the given expression is the <em>difference of squares</em> and 
we will need to make <alert>two</alert> factorizations</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {81y^{4}-16} \amp  = ({9y}^2)^2-4^2\\
                            \amp  = {\left(9y^{2}-4\right)\mathopen{}\left(9y^{2}+4\right)}\\
                            \amp  = {\left(3y-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(3y+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(9y^{2}+4\right)}
            \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
